### Health Check
GET http://localhost:4000/health

###

### ============================================
### PRODUCTS (JS Lambda)
### ============================================

### List All Products
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "{ listProducts { id name price category stock } }"
}

###

### List Products by Category
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "{ listProducts(category: \"Electronics\") { id name price stock } }"
}

###

### Search Products
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "{ searchProducts(query: \"shoes\") { id name price category } }"
}

###

### Get Product by ID
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "{ getProduct(id: \"prod-001\") { id name description price category stock createdAt } }"
}

###

### Create Product
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "mutation { createProduct(input: { name: \"Mechanical Keyboard\", description: \"RGB backlit\", price: 149.99, category: \"Electronics\", stock: 60 }) { id name price category stock createdAt } }"
}

###

### Update Product
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "mutation { updateProduct(id: \"prod-001\", input: { price: 179.99, stock: 45 }) { id name price stock updatedAt } }"
}

###

### Delete Product
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "mutation { deleteProduct(id: \"prod-004\") }"
}

###

### ============================================
### PAYMENTS (.NET Lambda)
### ============================================

### Charge Payment
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "mutation { chargePayment(input: { orderId: \"order-1\", amount: 199.99, currency: \"USD\", paymentMethod: \"card_visa_4242\" }) { id orderId amount currency status paymentMethod transactionId createdAt } }"
}

###

### Get Payment (use ID from charge above)
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "query GetPayment($id: ID!) { getPayment(id: $id) { id orderId amount currency status transactionId createdAt refundedAt } }",
  "variables": { "id": "REPLACE_WITH_PAYMENT_ID" }
}

###

### List Payments for Order
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "{ listPayments(orderId: \"order-1\") { id amount currency status transactionId createdAt } }"
}

###

### Refund Payment (full)
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "mutation RefundPayment($input: RefundPaymentInput!) { refundPayment(input: $input) { id amount status refundedAt refundReason } }",
  "variables": {
    "input": {
      "paymentId": "REPLACE_WITH_PAYMENT_ID",
      "reason": "Customer requested refund"
    }
  }
}

###

### Refund Payment (partial)
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "mutation RefundPayment($input: RefundPaymentInput!) { refundPayment(input: $input) { id amount status refundedAt refundReason } }",
  "variables": {
    "input": {
      "paymentId": "REPLACE_WITH_PAYMENT_ID",
      "amount": 50.00,
      "reason": "Partial refund - item returned"
    }
  }
}

###

### Charge Payment - Should Fail (amount > 10000)
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "mutation { chargePayment(input: { orderId: \"order-2\", amount: 15000, currency: \"USD\", paymentMethod: \"card_visa\" }) { id status } }"
}

###

### ============================================
### ORDERS (JS Lambda + .NET Lambda)
### ============================================

### Create Order (JS Lambda)
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "mutation { createOrder(input: { userId: \"user-1\", items: [{ productId: \"prod-001\", quantity: 1, price: 199.99 }, { productId: \"prod-003\", quantity: 2, price: 49.99 }] }) { id userId items { productId quantity price } total status createdAt } }"
}

###

### Process Order (.NET Lambda)
POST http://localhost:4000/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "mutation { processOrder(id: \"order-1\") { id status createdAt } }"
}

